								<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-763ab3a elementor-view-default elementor-widget elementor-widget-wgl-toggle-accordion" data-id="763ab3a" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="wgl-toggle-accordion.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
			<div class="wgl-accordion icon-plus" id="wgl-accordion-763ab3a" data-type="toggle"><div class="accordion__panel"><h4 id="accordion__header-1231" class="accordion__header" data-default=""><span class="accordion__title">Is it possible to utilize my subscription on multiple devices?</span><i class="accordion__icon elementor-icon "></i></h4><div class="accordion__content"><p>Each subscription is designed for exclusive use on a single device. If you'd like to use our service on multiple devices, we suggest getting separate subscriptions for each device to ensure smooth viewing.</p></div></div><div class="accordion__panel"><h4 id="accordion__header-1232" class="accordion__header" data-default=""><span class="accordion__title">Upon making a payment, does my subscription become active right away?</span><i class="accordion__icon elementor-icon "></i></h4><div class="accordion__content"><p><span>Your subscription becomes active upon receiving your activation credentials via email. For instance, if you subscribed for 3 months on February 1st at 11:55 pm and received your activation credentials on February 2nd at 00:10 am, your subscription commences from February 2nd at 00:10 am, extending for the next 3 months.</span></p></div></div><div class="accordion__panel"><h4 id="accordion__header-1233" class="accordion__header" data-default=""><span class="accordion__title">How do I verify the speed and quality of my internet connection?</span><i class="accordion__icon elementor-icon "></i></h4><div class="accordion__content"><p><span>Kindly utilize the speed test server provided below to assess your internet connection. It is recommended to conduct multiple tests at different times throughout the day for a comprehensive understanding of your overall internet speed. Please note that a stable minimum speed of 16 Mbps is required for optimal performance.</span></p><p><span>Speed Test Link: </span><a href="https://www.speedtest.net/" target="_new">https://www.speedtest.net/</a></p></div></div><div class="accordion__panel"><h4 id="accordion__header-1234" class="accordion__header" data-default=""><span class="accordion__title">If certain channels experience freezing, buffering, or intermittent issues, what should be done?</span><i class="accordion__icon elementor-icon "></i></h4><div class="accordion__content"><p><span>While the majority of our servers maintain stability, occasional freezing or disruptions in certain channels may occur for various reasons. It's important to note that these issues are typically temporary and our dedicated team of expert engineers is continuously working to resolve them. The common causes include fluctuations in customer internet, issues with the box/apps/customer setup, challenges with your ISP, temporary channel outages from the server end, and periodic server updates/restarts for performance enhancement conducted on a weekly basis.</span></p></div></div><div class="accordion__panel"><h4 id="accordion__header-1235" class="accordion__header" data-default=""><span class="accordion__title">Which payment methods are currently supported?</span><i class="accordion__icon elementor-icon "></i></h4><div class="accordion__content"><p><span>We welcome payments through PayPal, VISA, MasterCard, American Express, Skrill, Neteller, Webmoney, Bitcoin, and various other cryptocurrencies.</span></p></div></div><div class="accordion__panel"><h4 id="accordion__header-1236" class="accordion__header" data-default=""><span class="accordion__title">What can be done if my channel is encountering buffering problems?</span><i class="accordion__icon elementor-icon "></i></h4><div class="accordion__content"><p>Buffering may occur due to low internet speed or high internet traffic.</p><p>Cause: The primary reason for buffering is often a slow internet connection, which can be attributed to low speed or excessive bandwidth usage by other users in your household.</p><p>If multiple users are active, consider disconnecting them and trying again. Another factor is the use of Wi-Fi, which may not be optimal for uninterrupted TV watching.</p><p>Resolution: For a smoother experience, connect directly to your router using a LAN (Ethernet) cable or a power-line adapter. If this isn't feasible, try relocating the box closer to the router. Adjust your Wi-Fi channel to minimize interference with nearby devices. In case of buffering, press "pause" for 10-15 seconds and then resume, often resolving the need for buffering.</p></div></div></div>		</div>
